SIMPLE: inauguration
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inauguration
<hw>In*au`gu*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inauguratio</ets> a beginning: cf. F.
<ets>inauguration</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of inaugurating, or inducting into office
with solemnity; investiture by appropriate ceremonies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At his regal <qex>inauguration</qex>, his old father resigned the
kingdom to him.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The formal beginning or initiation of any movement,
course of action, etc.; <as>as, the <ex>inauguration</ex> of a new
system, a new condition, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inauguration Day</ent>⟦br⟧
